templates.description:
Ceragon IP50 E-band radio link monitoring template.
Covers IF-MIB interface statistics and Ceragon proprietary radio performance metrics.
Compatible with IP50EX, IP50EX-P, IP50CX models sharing enterprise OID 1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.

Radio OID map (confirmed on IP50EX-P FW 13.1.0, ifIndex 268451905):
  RSL (dBm, integer):         1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.1.1.2.{ifIndex}
  TX Power (dBm, integer):    1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.1.1.3.{ifIndex}
  TX Frequency (kHz):         1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.3.{ifIndex}
  RX Frequency (kHz):         1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.4.{ifIndex}
  Capacity (Mbps, Gauge32):   1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.16.{ifIndex}
  TX Modulation (integer):    1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.19.{ifIndex}
  RX Modulation (integer):    1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.21.{ifIndex}
  RSL MIMO/diversity (dBm):   1.3.6.1.4.1.2281.10.5.2.1.22.{ifIndex}

Note: Modulation valuemap codes (unverified — need confirmation from Ceragon MIB or device output at known modulation).
Note: Capacity at .10.5.2.1.16 reported as 600 on test device — assumed Mbps but needs MIB confirmation.
Note: RSL MIMO at .10.5.2.1.22 = -68 dBm on test device while main RSL = -35 dBm — likely XPIC/diversity channel.

